The Charles County Commissioners shall report to the General Assembly on or before August 1 each year, subject to § 2-1246 of the State Government Article, on the following items, for the preceding fiscal year:
The amount of the tax set by the Charles County Commissioners for each dwelling type;
The amount of proceeds derived from the issuance and sale of the county's new school capacity construction bonds;
The number of parcels of real property improved by new residential development in Charles County; and
The number of square feet of new public school capacity approved for construction in Charles County by the Interagency Committee on School Construction.
